<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2006-06-30</DATELINE><TITLE>Why Aging T Cells Fail: Implications for Vaccination</TITLE><BODY>Summary The decline in CD4+ T cell function with aging contributes to reduced vaccine efficacy. In this commentary, we discuss the factors leading to age-related changes in T cell function and propose how they may be overcome to enhance vaccine efficacy for the elderly.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>